My name is Abdullah Zahid, hailing from Pakistan, I am an avid learner with Bachelor Degrees in Computer Science and Economics from the University of Miami.

I started my journey programming arduinos and raspberrypis for small household purposes, like a bluetooth lock, or clap lights. immediately got hooked to what is now my motto: "Solving problems through programming"

Majority of my interests lie in Machine Learning, more specifically, in Natural Language processing, although predictive modeling is quite lucrative for me as well. I am also a web-development enthusiast and fullstack developer specializing in the MERN stack. My goto language is Python for nearly everything but have experience using Java, C and C++.

Apart from my hobbies listed above, electronic music is another one I am passionate about and DJ at my Fraternity: Alpha Sigma Phi. I am also an active participant and co-founder of the philanthropy "Adopt a Child", information about which can be found on the homepage.

If you are interested in getting in touch with me feel free to send me an email through the "Contact Me" tab on the top right of this page!

); } export default AboutPage;
